            <fr:title text="Schemes from image finite posets">Schemes from image finite posets</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="/topl-Q322/" title="Image finite posets" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-Q322/" display-uri="topl-Q322" type="local">image finite poset</fr:link>. Recall from <fr:link href="/topl-GIFJ/" title="Image finite posets are locally spectral" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-GIFJ/" display-uri="topl-GIFJ" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-GIFJ/" display-uri="topl-GIFJ" /></fr:link> that as a topological space it is <fr:link href="/topl-VV9N/" title="Spectral spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-VV9N/" display-uri="topl-VV9N" type="local">locally spectral</fr:link>. It is a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>13</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  We need to define a structural sheaf on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. For any upward closed susbet <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, we define 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathcal {O}_{X}(U) := \mathcal {U}(U), ]]></fr:tex>
  the distributive lattice of upward closed subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>. This is a sheaf, because if we have a union <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U = \bigcup _{i\in  I}U_i]]></fr:tex> with an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V_i \in  \mathcal {O}_{X}(U_i)]]></fr:tex>, which is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V_i \subseteq  U_i]]></fr:tex> upward closed, which agrees on intersections,
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ V_i \cap  U_j = V_j \cap  U_i, ]]></fr:tex>
  then there is a unique <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V \subseteq  U]]></fr:tex> given by 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ V = \bigcup _{i\in  I}V_i, ]]></fr:tex>
  such that 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ V \cap  U_j = \bigcup _{i\in  I}V_i \cap  U_j = \bigcup _{i\in  I}V_j \cap  U_i = V_j \cap  \bigcup _{i\in  I}U_i = V_j \cap  U = V_j. ]]></fr:tex>
  This is in fact a <fr:link href="/schm-V16H/" title="Locally distributed space" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-V16H/" display-uri="schm-V16H" type="local">locally distributed space</fr:link>, because for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>,
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathcal {O}_{X,x} \cong  \mathcal {O}_{X}(\uparrow  x) \cong  \mathcal {U}(\uparrow  x), ]]></fr:tex>
  which is <fr:link href="/idem-comm-75C1/" title="Local distributive lattice" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-75C1/" display-uri="idem-comm-75C1" type="local">local</fr:link> because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\uparrow  x]]></fr:tex> has a root (cf. <fr:link href="/idem-comm-E2I8/" title="Equivalent formulation of locality" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-E2I8/" display-uri="idem-comm-E2I8" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-E2I8/" display-uri="idem-comm-E2I8" /></fr:link>). Finally, this is a scheme, because by construction for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>, the open neighbourhood <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\uparrow  x]]></fr:tex> is affine <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\uparrow  x,\mathcal {O}_{\uparrow  x}) \cong  \operatorname {Spec}\mathcal {U}(\uparrow  x)]]></fr:tex>.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
